# Mastra Agent Guidelines

## Agent Definition
- Always use `new Agent()` from `@mastra/core/agent`
- Name agents with descriptive nouns (e.g., `supportAgent`, `researchAssistant`)
- Keep instructions concise and role-focused
- Use dynamic instructions only when behavior changes per-user

## Code Style
```ts
export const agentName = new Agent({
  name: "agent-name",
  description: "What this agent does", // Required for MCP exposure
  instructions: "You are a [role]. You [key behaviors].",
  model: openai("gpt-4o-mini"),
  tools: { toolOne, toolTwo },
});
```

## Tool Usage
- Import tools explicitly; never define tools inline
- Group related tools in the `tools` object
- Use dynamic tools only for user-specific access control
- Prefer tool composition over large multi-purpose tools

## Memory Configuration
- Always use the new memory parameter format
- Provide both `thread` and `resource` when using memory
- Configure memory options explicitly for predictable behavior

```ts
await agent.generate("Hello", {
  memory: {
    thread: "thread-123",
    resource: "user-456",
    options: { lastMessages: 10 }
  }
});
```

## Best Practices
- One agent per file in `src/mastra/agents/`
- Export agents as named exports
- Keep agent instructions under 500 characters
- Use structured output (`output` or `experimental_output`) for predictable responses
- Set `maxSteps` based on expected tool usage (default: 1)
- Use `onStepFinish` for debugging multi-step operations

## Anti-Patterns
- Don't implement retry logic in instructions
- Don't reference other agents in instructions
- Don't use agents for simple data transformation
- Don't create "controller" agents that orchestrate other agents
- Avoid runtime agent creation; define agents at module level

## Summary
- Use `new Agent()` from `@mastra/core/agent`
- Combine LLM, tools, and memory for intelligent responses
- Always provide `resourceId` and `threadId` for memory to work
- Enable memory with `memory: new Memory()` for conversation context
- Use `generate()` for single responses, `stream()` for real-time output
- Limit tool iterations with `maxSteps` parameter
- Store in `src/mastra/agents/` with descriptive names